46 #ifdef USE_SIMULATOR
47 unsigned SimulatorFeaturesFromCommandLine() {
48  if (strcmp(v8_flags.sim_arm64_optional_features, "none") == 0) {
49  return 0;
50  }
51  if (strcmp(v8_flags.sim_arm64_optional_features, "all") == 0) {
52  return (1u << NUMBER_OF_CPU_FEATURES) - 1;
53  }
54  fprintf(
55  stderr,
56  "Error: unrecognised value for --sim-arm64-optional-features ('%s').\n",
57  v8_flags.sim_arm64_optional_features.value());
58  fprintf(stderr,
59  "Supported values are: none\n"
60  " all\n");
61  FATAL("sim-arm64-optional-features");
62 }
63 #endif // USE_SIMULATOR
64 
65 constexpr unsigned CpuFeaturesFromCompiler() {
66  unsigned features = 0;
67 #if defined(__ARM_FEATURE_JCVT) && !defined(V8_TARGET_OS_IOS)
68  features |= 1u << JSCVT;
69 #endif
70 #if defined(__ARM_FEATURE_DOTPROD)
71  features |= 1u << DOTPROD;
72 #endif
73 #if defined(__ARM_FEATURE_SHA3)
74  features |= 1u << SHA3;
75 #endif
76 #if defined(__ARM_FEATURE_ATOMICS)
77  features |= 1u << LSE;
78 #endif
79 // There is no __ARM_FEATURE_PMULL macro; instead, __ARM_FEATURE_AES
80 // covers the FEAT_PMULL feature too.
81 #if defined(__ARM_FEATURE_AES)
82  features |= 1u << PMULL1Q;
83 #endif
84 #if defined(__ARM_FEATURE_HBC)
85  features |= 1u << HBC;
86 #endif
87  return features;
88 }
89 
90 constexpr unsigned CpuFeaturesFromTargetOS() {
91  unsigned features = 0;
92 #if defined(V8_TARGET_OS_MACOS) && !defined(V8_TARGET_OS_IOS)
93  // TODO(v8:13004): Detect if an iPhone is new enough to support jscvt, dotprot
94  // and lse.
95  features |= 1u << JSCVT;
96  features |= 1u << DOTPROD;
97  features |= 1u << LSE;
98  features |= 1u << PMULL1Q;
99 #endif
100  return features;
101 }
102 
103 } // namespace

105 // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
106 // CpuFeatures implementation.
107 bool CpuFeatures::SupportsWasmSimd128() { return true; }
108 
109 void CpuFeatures::ProbeImpl(bool cross_compile) {
110  // Only use statically determined features for cross compile (snapshot).
111  if (cross_compile) {
112  supported_ |= CpuFeaturesFromCompiler();
113  supported_ |= CpuFeaturesFromTargetOS();
114  return;
115  }
116 
117  // We used to probe for coherent cache support, but on older CPUs it
118  // causes crashes (crbug.com/524337), and newer CPUs don't even have
119  // the feature any more.
120 
121 #ifdef USE_SIMULATOR
122  supported_ |= SimulatorFeaturesFromCommandLine();
123 #else
124  // Probe for additional features at runtime.
125  base::CPU cpu;
126  unsigned runtime = 0;
127  if (cpu.has_jscvt()) {
128  runtime |= 1u << JSCVT;
129  }
130  if (cpu.has_dot_prod()) {
131  runtime |= 1u << DOTPROD;
132  }
133  if (cpu.has_sha3()) {
134  runtime |= 1u << SHA3;
135  }
136  if (cpu.has_lse()) {
137  runtime |= 1u << LSE;
138  }
139  if (cpu.has_pmull1q()) {
140  runtime |= 1u << PMULL1Q;
141  }
142  if (cpu.has_fp16()) {
143  runtime |= 1u << FP16;
144  }
145  if (cpu.has_hbc()) {
146  runtime |= 1u << HBC;
147  }
148  if (cpu.has_cssc()) {
149  runtime |= 1u << CSSC;
150  }
151 
152  // Use the best of the features found by CPU detection and those inferred from
153  // the build system.
154  supported_ |= CpuFeaturesFromCompiler();
155  supported_ |= runtime;
156 #endif // USE_SIMULATOR
157 
158  // Set a static value on whether Simd is supported.
159  // This variable is only used for certain archs to query SupportWasmSimd128()
160  // at runtime in builtins using an extern ref. Other callers should use
161  // CpuFeatures::SupportWasmSimd128().
162  CpuFeatures::supports_wasm_simd_128_ = CpuFeatures::SupportsWasmSimd128();
163 }
164 
165 void CpuFeatures::PrintTarget() {}
166 void CpuFeatures::PrintFeatures() {}

168 // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
169 // CPURegList utilities.
170 
171 CPURegister CPURegList::PopLowestIndex() {
172  if (IsEmpty()) {
173  return NoCPUReg;
174  }
175  int index = base::bits::CountTrailingZeros(list_);
176  DCHECK((1LL << index) & list_);
177  Remove(index);
178  return CPURegister::Create(index, size_, type_);
179 }
180 
181 CPURegister CPURegList::PopHighestIndex() {
182  if (IsEmpty()) {
183  return NoCPUReg;
184  }
185  int index = CountLeadingZeros(list_, kRegListSizeInBits);
186  index = kRegListSizeInBits - 1 - index;
187  DCHECK((1LL << index) & list_);
188  Remove(index);
189  return CPURegister::Create(index, size_, type_);
190 }
191 
192 void CPURegList::Align() {
193  // Use padreg, if necessary, to maintain stack alignment.
194  if (Count() % 2 != 0) {
195  if (IncludesAliasOf(padreg)) {
196  Remove(padreg);
197  } else {
198  Combine(padreg);
199  }
200  }
201 
202  DCHECK_EQ(Count() % 2, 0);
203 }
204 
205 CPURegList CPURegList::GetCalleeSaved(int size) {
206  return CPURegList(CPURegister::kRegister, size, 19, 28);
207 }
208 
209 CPURegList CPURegList::GetCalleeSavedV(int size) {
210  return CPURegList(CPURegister::kVRegister, size, 8, 15);
211 }
212 
213 CPURegList CPURegList::GetCallerSaved(int size) {
214  // x18 is the platform register and is reserved for the use of platform ABIs.
215  // Registers x0-x17 are caller-saved.
216  CPURegList list = CPURegList(CPURegister::kRegister, size, 0, 17);
217  return list;
218 }
219 
220 CPURegList CPURegList::GetCallerSavedV(int size) {
221  // Registers d0-d7 and d16-d31 are caller-saved.
222  CPURegList list = CPURegList(CPURegister::kVRegister, size, 0, 7);
223  list.Combine(CPURegList(CPURegister::kVRegister, size, 16, 31));
224  return list;
225 }

229 
230 const int RelocInfo::kApplyMask =
231  RelocInfo::ModeMask(RelocInfo::CODE_TARGET) |
232  RelocInfo::ModeMask(RelocInfo::NEAR_BUILTIN_ENTRY) |
233  RelocInfo::ModeMask(RelocInfo::INTERNAL_REFERENCE) |
234  RelocInfo::ModeMask(RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
235 
236 bool RelocInfo::IsCodedSpecially() {
237  // The deserializer needs to know whether a pointer is specially coded. Being
238  // specially coded on ARM64 means that it is an immediate branch.
239  Instruction* instr = reinterpret_cast<Instruction*>(pc_);
240  if (instr->IsLdrLiteralX()) {
241  return false;
242  } else {
243  DCHECK(instr->IsBranchAndLink() || instr->IsUnconditionalBranch());
244  return true;
245  }
246 }
247 
248 bool RelocInfo::IsInConstantPool() {
249  Instruction* instr = reinterpret_cast<Instruction*>(pc_);
250  DCHECK_IMPLIES(instr->IsLdrLiteralW(), COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL);
251  return instr->IsLdrLiteralX() ||
252  (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL && instr->IsLdrLiteralW());
253 }
254 
255 uint32_t RelocInfo::wasm_call_tag() const {
256  DCHECK(rmode_ == WASM_CALL || rmode_ == WASM_STUB_CALL);
257  Instruction* instr = reinterpret_cast<Instruction*>(pc_);
258  if (instr->IsLdrLiteralX()) {
259  return static_cast<uint32_t>(
260  Memory<Address>(Assembler::target_pointer_address_at(pc_)));
261  } else {
262  DCHECK(instr->IsBranchAndLink() || instr->IsUnconditionalBranch());
263  return static_cast<uint32_t>(instr->ImmPCOffset() / kInstrSize);
264  }
265 }
266 
267 bool AreAliased(const CPURegister& reg1, const CPURegister& reg2,
268  const CPURegister& reg3, const CPURegister& reg4,
269  const CPURegister& reg5, const CPURegister& reg6,
270  const CPURegister& reg7, const CPURegister& reg8) {
271  int number_of_valid_regs = 0;
272  int number_of_valid_fpregs = 0;
273 
274  uint64_t unique_regs = 0;
275  uint64_t unique_fpregs = 0;
276 
277  const CPURegister regs[] = {reg1, reg2, reg3, reg4, reg5, reg6, reg7, reg8};
278 
279  for (unsigned i = 0; i < arraysize(regs); i++) {
280  if (regs[i].IsRegister()) {
281  number_of_valid_regs++;
282  unique_regs |= (uint64_t{1} << regs[i].code());
283  } else if (regs[i].IsVRegister()) {
284  number_of_valid_fpregs++;
285  unique_fpregs |= (uint64_t{1} << regs[i].code());
286  } else {
287  DCHECK(!regs[i].is_valid());
288  }
289  }
290 
291  int number_of_unique_regs =
292  CountSetBits(unique_regs, sizeof(unique_regs) * kBitsPerByte);
293  int number_of_unique_fpregs =
294  CountSetBits(unique_fpregs, sizeof(unique_fpregs) * kBitsPerByte);
295 
296  DCHECK(number_of_valid_regs >= number_of_unique_regs);
297  DCHECK(number_of_valid_fpregs >= number_of_unique_fpregs);
298 
299  return (number_of_valid_regs != number_of_unique_regs) ||
300  (number_of_valid_fpregs != number_of_unique_fpregs);
301 }
302 
303 bool AreSameSizeAndType(const CPURegister& reg1, const CPURegister& reg2,
304  const CPURegister& reg3, const CPURegister& reg4,
305  const CPURegister& reg5, const CPURegister& reg6,
306  const CPURegister& reg7, const CPURegister& reg8) {
307  DCHECK(reg1.is_valid());
308  bool match = true;
309  match &= !reg2.is_valid() || reg2.IsSameSizeAndType(reg1);
310  match &= !reg3.is_valid() || reg3.IsSameSizeAndType(reg1);
311  match &= !reg4.is_valid() || reg4.IsSameSizeAndType(reg1);
312  match &= !reg5.is_valid() || reg5.IsSameSizeAndType(reg1);
313  match &= !reg6.is_valid() || reg6.IsSameSizeAndType(reg1);
314  match &= !reg7.is_valid() || reg7.IsSameSizeAndType(reg1);
315  match &= !reg8.is_valid() || reg8.IsSameSizeAndType(reg1);
316  return match;
317 }
318 
319 bool AreSameFormat(const Register& reg1, const Register& reg2,
320  const Register& reg3, const Register& reg4) {
321  DCHECK(reg1.is_valid());
322  return (!reg2.is_valid() || reg2.IsSameSizeAndType(reg1)) &&
323  (!reg3.is_valid() || reg3.IsSameSizeAndType(reg1)) &&
324  (!reg4.is_valid() || reg4.IsSameSizeAndType(reg1));
325 }
326 
327 bool AreSameFormat(const VRegister& reg1, const VRegister& reg2,
328  const VRegister& reg3, const VRegister& reg4) {
329  DCHECK(reg1.is_valid());
330  return (!reg2.is_valid() || reg2.IsSameFormat(reg1)) &&
331  (!reg3.is_valid() || reg3.IsSameFormat(reg1)) &&
332  (!reg4.is_valid() || reg4.IsSameFormat(reg1));
333 }
334 
335 bool AreConsecutive(const CPURegister& reg1, const CPURegister& reg2,
336  const CPURegister& reg3, const CPURegister& reg4) {
337  DCHECK(reg1.is_valid());
338 
339  if (!reg2.is_valid()) {
340  DCHECK(!reg3.is_valid() && !reg4.is_valid());
341  return true;
342  } else if (reg2.code() != ((reg1.code() + 1) % (reg1.MaxCode() + 1))) {
343  return false;
344  }
345 
346  if (!reg3.is_valid()) {
347  DCHECK(!reg4.is_valid());
348  return true;
349  } else if (reg3.code() != ((reg2.code() + 1) % (reg1.MaxCode() + 1))) {
350  return false;
351  }
352 
353  if (!reg4.is_valid()) {
354  return true;
355  } else if (reg4.code() != ((reg3.code() + 1) % (reg1.MaxCode() + 1))) {
356  return false;
357  }
358 
359  return true;
360 }
361 
362 bool AreEven(const CPURegister& reg1, const CPURegister& reg2,
363  const CPURegister& reg3, const CPURegister& reg4,
364  const CPURegister& reg5, const CPURegister& reg6,
365  const CPURegister& reg7, const CPURegister& reg8) {
366  DCHECK(reg1.is_valid());
367  bool even = reg1.IsEven();
368  even &= !reg2.is_valid() || reg2.IsEven();
369  even &= !reg3.is_valid() || reg3.IsEven();
370  even &= !reg4.is_valid() || reg4.IsEven();
371  even &= !reg5.is_valid() || reg5.IsEven();
372  even &= !reg6.is_valid() || reg6.IsEven();
373  even &= !reg7.is_valid() || reg7.IsEven();
374  even &= !reg8.is_valid() || reg8.IsEven();
375  return even;
376 }

378 bool Operand::NeedsRelocation(const Assembler* assembler) const {
379  RelocInfo::Mode rmode = immediate_.rmode();
380 
381  if (RelocInfo::IsOnlyForSerializer(rmode)) {
382  return assembler->options().record_reloc_info_for_serialization;
383  }
384 
385  return !RelocInfo::IsNoInfo(rmode);
386 }

388 // Assembler
389 Assembler::Assembler(const MaybeAssemblerZone& zone,
390  const AssemblerOptions& options,
391  std::unique_ptr<AssemblerBuffer> buffer)
392  : AssemblerBase(options, std::move(buffer)),
393  zone_(zone),
394  unresolved_branches_(zone_.get()),
395  constpool_(this) {
396  Reset();
397 
398 #if defined(V8_OS_WIN)
399  if (options.collect_win64_unwind_info) {
400  xdata_encoder_ = std::make_unique<win64_unwindinfo::XdataEncoder>(*this);
401  }
402 #endif
403 }
404 
405 Assembler::~Assembler() {
406  DCHECK(constpool_.IsEmpty());
407  DCHECK_EQ(veneer_pool_blocked_nesting_, 0);
408 }
409 
410 void Assembler::AbortedCodeGeneration() { constpool_.Clear(); }
411 
412 void Assembler::Reset() {
413 #ifdef DEBUG
414  DCHECK((pc_ >= buffer_start_) && (pc_ < buffer_start_ + buffer_->size()));
415  DCHECK_EQ(veneer_pool_blocked_nesting_, 0);
416  DCHECK(unresolved_branches_.empty());
417  memset(buffer_start_, 0, pc_ - buffer_start_);
418 #endif
419  pc_ = buffer_start_;
420  reloc_info_writer.Reposition(buffer_start_ + buffer_->size(), pc_);
421  constpool_.Clear();
422  constpool_.SetNextCheckIn(ConstantPool::kCheckInterval);
423  next_veneer_pool_check_ = kMaxInt;
424 }
425 
426 #if defined(V8_OS_WIN)
427 win64_unwindinfo::BuiltinUnwindInfo Assembler::GetUnwindInfo() const {
428  DCHECK(options().collect_win64_unwind_info);
429  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(xdata_encoder_);
430  return xdata_encoder_->unwinding_info();
431 }
432 #endif

434 void Assembler::AllocateAndInstallRequestedHeapNumbers(LocalIsolate* isolate) {
435  DCHECK_IMPLIES(isolate == nullptr, heap_number_requests_.empty());
436  for (auto& request : heap_number_requests_) {
437  Address pc = reinterpret_cast<Address>(buffer_start_) + request.offset();
438  Handle<HeapObject> object =
439  isolate->factory()->NewHeapNumber<AllocationType::kOld>(
440  request.heap_number());
441  EmbeddedObjectIndex index = AddEmbeddedObject(object);
442  set_embedded_object_index_referenced_from(pc, index);
443  }
444 }
445 
446 void Assembler::GetCode(Isolate* isolate, CodeDesc* desc) {
447  GetCode(isolate->main_thread_local_isolate(), desc);
448 }
449 void Assembler::GetCode(LocalIsolate* isolate, CodeDesc* desc,
450  SafepointTableBuilderBase* safepoint_table_builder,
451  int handler_table_offset) {
452  // As a crutch to avoid having to add manual Align calls wherever we use a
453  // raw workflow to create InstructionStream objects (mostly in tests), add
454  // another Align call here. It does no harm - the end of the InstructionStream
455  // object is aligned to the (larger) kCodeAlignment anyways.
456  // TODO(jgruber): Consider moving responsibility for proper alignment to
457  // metadata table builders (safepoint, handler, constant pool, code
458  // comments).
459  DataAlign(InstructionStream::kMetadataAlignment);
460 
461  // Emit constant pool if necessary.
462  ForceConstantPoolEmissionWithoutJump();
463  DCHECK(constpool_.IsEmpty());
464 
465  const int code_comments_size = WriteCodeComments();
466  const int jump_table_info_size = WriteJumpTableInfos();
467 
468  AllocateAndInstallRequestedHeapNumbers(isolate);
469 
470  // Set up code descriptor.
471  // TODO(jgruber): Reconsider how these offsets and sizes are maintained up to
472  // this point to make CodeDesc initialization less fiddly.
473 
474  static constexpr int kConstantPoolSize = 0;
475  const int instruction_size = pc_offset();
476  const int jump_table_info_offset = instruction_size - jump_table_info_size;
477  const int code_comments_offset = jump_table_info_offset - code_comments_size;
478  const int constant_pool_offset = code_comments_offset - kConstantPoolSize;
479  const int handler_table_offset2 = (handler_table_offset == kNoHandlerTable)
480  ? constant_pool_offset
481  : handler_table_offset;
482  const int safepoint_table_offset =
483  (safepoint_table_builder == kNoSafepointTable)
484  ? handler_table_offset2
485  : safepoint_table_builder->safepoint_table_offset();
486  const int reloc_info_offset =
487  static_cast<int>(reloc_info_writer.pos() - buffer_->start());
488  CodeDesc::Initialize(desc, this, safepoint_table_offset,
489  handler_table_offset2, constant_pool_offset,
490  code_comments_offset, jump_table_info_offset,
491  reloc_info_offset);
492 }
493 
494 void Assembler::Align(int m) {
495  // If not, the loop below won't terminate.
496  DCHECK(IsAligned(pc_offset(), kInstrSize));
497  DCHECK(m >= kInstrSize && base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(m));
498  while ((pc_offset() & (m - 1)) != 0) {
499  nop();
500  }
501 }
502 
503 void Assembler::CodeTargetAlign() {
504  // Preferred alignment of jump targets on some ARM chips.
505 #if !defined(V8_TARGET_OS_MACOS)
506  Align(8);
507 #endif
508 }
509 
510 void Assembler::CheckLabelLinkChain(Label const* label) {
511 #ifdef DEBUG
512  if (label->is_linked()) {
513  static const int kMaxLinksToCheck = 64; // Avoid O(n2) behaviour.
514  int links_checked = 0;
515  int64_t linkoffset = label->pos();
516  bool end_of_chain = false;
517  while (!end_of_chain) {
518  if (++links_checked > kMaxLinksToCheck) break;
519  Instruction* link = InstructionAt(linkoffset);
520  int64_t linkpcoffset = link->ImmPCOffset();
521  int64_t prevlinkoffset = linkoffset + linkpcoffset;
522 
523  end_of_chain = (linkoffset == prevlinkoffset);
524  linkoffset = linkoffset + linkpcoffset;
525  }
526  }
527 #endif
528 }
529 
530 void Assembler::RemoveBranchFromLabelLinkChain(Instruction* branch,
531  Label* label,
532  Instruction* label_veneer) {
533  DCHECK(label->is_linked());
534 
535  CheckLabelLinkChain(label);
536 
537  Instruction* link = InstructionAt(label->pos());
538  Instruction* prev_link = link;
539  Instruction* next_link;
540 
541  if (link != branch) {
542  int i = static_cast<int>(InstructionOffset(branch));
543  // Currently, we don't support adr instructions sharing labels with
544  // branches in the link chain.
545  DCHECK(branch_link_chain_back_edge_.contains(i));
546  prev_link = InstructionAt(branch_link_chain_back_edge_.at(i));
547  link = branch;
548  }
549 
550  DCHECK(branch == link);
551  next_link = branch->ImmPCOffsetTarget();
552 
553  if (branch == prev_link) {
554  // The branch is the first instruction in the chain.
555  if (branch == next_link) {
556  // It is also the last instruction in the chain, so it is the only branch
557  // currently referring to this label.
558  //
559  // Label -> this branch -> start
560  label->Unuse();
561  } else {
562  // Label -> this branch -> 1+ branches -> start
563  label->link_to(static_cast<int>(InstructionOffset(next_link)));
564  branch_link_chain_back_edge_.erase(
565  static_cast<int>(InstructionOffset(next_link)));
566  }
567  } else if (branch == next_link) {
568  // The branch is the last (but not also the first) instruction in the chain.
569  //
570  // Label -> 1+ branches -> this branch -> start
571  prev_link->SetImmPCOffsetTarget(zone(), options(), prev_link);
572  branch_link_chain_back_edge_.erase(
573  static_cast<int>(InstructionOffset(branch)));
574  } else {
575  // The branch is in the middle of the chain.
576  //
577  // Label -> 1+ branches -> this branch -> 1+ branches -> start
578  int n = static_cast<int>(InstructionOffset(next_link));
579  if (branch_link_chain_back_edge_.contains(n)) {
580  // Update back edge such that the branch after this branch points to the
581  // branch before it.
582  branch_link_chain_back_edge_[n] =
583  static_cast<int>(InstructionOffset(prev_link));
584  branch_link_chain_back_edge_.erase(
585  static_cast<int>(InstructionOffset(branch)));
586  }
587 
588  if (prev_link->IsTargetInImmPCOffsetRange(next_link)) {
589  prev_link->SetImmPCOffsetTarget(zone(), options(), next_link);
590  } else if (label_veneer != nullptr) {
591  // Use the veneer for all previous links in the chain.
592  prev_link->SetImmPCOffsetTarget(zone(), options(), prev_link);
593 
594  bool end_of_chain = false;
595  link = next_link;
596  while (!end_of_chain) {
597  next_link = link->ImmPCOffsetTarget();
598  end_of_chain = (link == next_link);
599  link->SetImmPCOffsetTarget(zone(), options(), label_veneer);
600  // {link} is now resolved; remove it from {unresolved_branches_} so
601  // we won't later try to process it again, which would fail because
602  // by walking the chain of its label's unresolved branch instructions,
603  // we won't find it: {prev_link} is now the end of that chain after
604  // its update above.
605  if (link->IsCondBranchImm() || link->IsCompareBranch()) {
606  static_assert(Instruction::ImmBranchRange(CondBranchType) ==
607  Instruction::ImmBranchRange(CompareBranchType));
608  int max_reachable_pc = static_cast<int>(InstructionOffset(link)) +
609  Instruction::ImmBranchRange(CondBranchType);
610  unresolved_branches_.erase(max_reachable_pc);
611  } else if (link->IsTestBranch()) {
612  // Add 1 to account for branch type tag bit.
613  int max_reachable_pc = static_cast<int>(InstructionOffset(link)) +
614  Instruction::ImmBranchRange(TestBranchType) +
615  1;
616  unresolved_branches_.erase(max_reachable_pc);
617  } else {
618  // Other branch types are not handled by veneers.
619  }
620  link = next_link;
621  }
622  } else {
623  // The assert below will fire.
624  // Some other work could be attempted to fix up the chain, but it would be
625  // rather complicated. If we crash here, we may want to consider using an
626  // other mechanism than a chain of branches.
627  //
628  // Note that this situation currently should not happen, as we always call
629  // this function with a veneer to the target label.
630  // However this could happen with a MacroAssembler in the following state:
631  // [previous code]
632  // B(label);
633  // [20KB code]
634  // Tbz(label); // First tbz. Pointing to unconditional branch.
635  // [20KB code]
636  // Tbz(label); // Second tbz. Pointing to the first tbz.
637  // [more code]
638  // and this function is called to remove the first tbz from the label link
639  // chain. Since tbz has a range of +-32KB, the second tbz cannot point to
640  // the unconditional branch.
641  CHECK(prev_link->IsTargetInImmPCOffsetRange(next_link));
642  UNREACHABLE();
643  }
644  }
645 
646  CheckLabelLinkChain(label);
647 }
648 
649 void Assembler::bind(Label* label) {
650  // Bind label to the address at pc_. All instructions (most likely branches)
651  // that are linked to this label will be updated to point to the newly-bound
652  // label.
653 
654  DCHECK(!label->is_near_linked());
655  DCHECK(!label->is_bound());
656 
657  DeleteUnresolvedBranchInfoForLabel(label);
658 
659  // If the label is linked, the link chain looks something like this:
660  //
661  // |--I----I-------I-------L
662  // |---------------------->| pc_offset
663  // |-------------->| linkoffset = label->pos()
664  // |<------| link->ImmPCOffset()
665  // |------>| prevlinkoffset = linkoffset + link->ImmPCOffset()
666  //
667  // On each iteration, the last link is updated and then removed from the
668  // chain until only one remains. At that point, the label is bound.
669  //
670  // If the label is not linked, no preparation is required before binding.
671  while (label->is_linked()) {
672  int linkoffset = label->pos();
673  Instruction* link = InstructionAt(linkoffset);
674  int prevlinkoffset = linkoffset + static_cast<int>(link->ImmPCOffset());
675 
676  CheckLabelLinkChain(label);
677 
678  DCHECK_GE(linkoffset, 0);
679  DCHECK(linkoffset < pc_offset());
680  DCHECK((linkoffset > prevlinkoffset) ||
681  (linkoffset - prevlinkoffset == kStartOfLabelLinkChain));
682  DCHECK_GE(prevlinkoffset, 0);
683 
684  // Update the link to point to the label.
685  if (link->IsUnresolvedInternalReference()) {
686  // Internal references do not get patched to an instruction but directly
687  // to an address.
688  internal_reference_positions_.push_back(linkoffset);
689  memcpy(link, &pc_, kSystemPointerSize);
690  } else {
691  link->SetImmPCOffsetTarget(zone(), options(),
692  reinterpret_cast<Instruction*>(pc_));
693 
694  // Discard back edge data for this link.
695  branch_link_chain_back_edge_.erase(
696  static_cast<int>(InstructionOffset(link)));
697  }
698 
699  // Link the label to the previous link in the chain.
700  if (linkoffset - prevlinkoffset == kStartOfLabelLinkChain) {
701  // We hit kStartOfLabelLinkChain, so the chain is fully processed.
702  label->Unuse();
703  } else {
704  // Update the label for the next iteration.
705  label->link_to(prevlinkoffset);
706  }
707  }
708  label->bind_to(pc_offset());
709 
710  DCHECK(label->is_bound());
711  DCHECK(!label->is_linked());
712 }
713 
714 int Assembler::LinkAndGetByteOffsetTo(Label* label) {
715  DCHECK_EQ(sizeof(*pc_), 1);
716  CheckLabelLinkChain(label);
717 
718  int offset;
719  if (label->is_bound()) {
720  // The label is bound, so it does not need to be updated. Referring
721  // instructions must link directly to the label as they will not be
722  // updated.
723  //
724  // In this case, label->pos() returns the offset of the label from the
725  // start of the buffer.
726  //
727  // Note that offset can be zero for self-referential instructions. (This
728  // could be useful for ADR, for example.)
729  offset = label->pos() - pc_offset();
730  DCHECK_LE(offset, 0);
731  } else {
732  if (label->is_linked()) {
733  // The label is linked, so the referring instruction should be added onto
734  // the end of the label's link chain.
735  //
736  // In this case, label->pos() returns the offset of the last linked
737  // instruction from the start of the buffer.
738  offset = label->pos() - pc_offset();
739  DCHECK_NE(offset, kStartOfLabelLinkChain);
740  // Note that the offset here needs to be PC-relative only so that the
741  // first instruction in a buffer can link to an unbound label. Otherwise,
742  // the offset would be 0 for this case, and 0 is reserved for
743  // kStartOfLabelLinkChain.
744  } else {
745  // The label is unused, so it now becomes linked and the referring
746  // instruction is at the start of the new link chain.
747  offset = kStartOfLabelLinkChain;
748  }
749  // The instruction at pc is now the last link in the label's chain.
750  label->link_to(pc_offset());
751  }
752 
753  return offset;
754 }
755 
756 void Assembler::DeleteUnresolvedBranchInfoForLabelTraverse(Label* label) {
757  DCHECK(label->is_linked());
758  CheckLabelLinkChain(label);
759 
760  int link_offset = label->pos();
761  int link_pcoffset;
762  bool end_of_chain = false;
763 
764  while (!end_of_chain) {
765  Instruction* link = InstructionAt(link_offset);
766  int max_reachable_pc = static_cast<int>(InstructionOffset(link));
767 
768  // ADR instructions and unconditional branches are not handled by veneers.
769  if (link->IsCondBranchImm() || link->IsCompareBranch()) {
770  static_assert(Instruction::ImmBranchRange(CondBranchType) ==
771  Instruction::ImmBranchRange(CompareBranchType));
772  max_reachable_pc += Instruction::ImmBranchRange(CondBranchType);
773  unresolved_branches_.erase(max_reachable_pc);
774  link_pcoffset = link->ImmCondBranch() * kInstrSize;
775  } else if (link->IsTestBranch()) {
776  // Add one to account for branch type tag bit.
777  max_reachable_pc += Instruction::ImmBranchRange(TestBranchType) + 1;
778  unresolved_branches_.erase(max_reachable_pc);
779  link_pcoffset = link->ImmTestBranch() * kInstrSize;
780  } else if (link->IsUncondBranchImm()) {
781  link_pcoffset = link->ImmUncondBranch() * kInstrSize;
782  } else {
783  link_pcoffset = static_cast<int>(link->ImmPCOffset());
784  }
785 
786  end_of_chain = (link_pcoffset == 0);
787  link_offset = link_offset + link_pcoffset;
788  }
789 }
790 
791 void Assembler::DeleteUnresolvedBranchInfoForLabel(Label* label) {
792  if (unresolved_branches_.empty()) {
793  DCHECK_EQ(next_veneer_pool_check_, kMaxInt);
794  return;
795  }
796 
797  if (label->is_linked()) {
798  // Branches to this label will be resolved when the label is bound, normally
799  // just after all the associated info has been deleted.
800  DeleteUnresolvedBranchInfoForLabelTraverse(label);
801  }
802  if (unresolved_branches_.empty()) {
803  next_veneer_pool_check_ = kMaxInt;
804  } else {
805  next_veneer_pool_check_ =
806  unresolved_branches_first_limit() - kVeneerDistanceCheckMargin;
807  }
808 }
809 
810 bool Assembler::IsConstantPoolAt(Instruction* instr) {
811  // The constant pool marker is made of two instructions. These instructions
812  // will never be emitted by the JIT, so checking for the first one is enough:
813  // 0: ldr xzr, #<size of pool>
814  bool result = instr->IsLdrLiteralX() && (instr->Rt() == kZeroRegCode);
815 
816  // It is still worth asserting the marker is complete.
817  // 4: blr xzr
818  DCHECK(!result || (instr->following()->IsBranchAndLinkToRegister() &&
819  instr->following()->Rn() == kZeroRegCode));
820 
821  return result;
822 }
823 
824 int Assembler::ConstantPoolSizeAt(Instruction* instr) {
825 #ifdef USE_SIMULATOR
826  // Assembler::debug() embeds constants directly into the instruction stream.
827  // Although this is not a genuine constant pool, treat it like one to avoid
828  // disassembling the constants.
829  if ((instr->Mask(ExceptionMask) == HLT) &&
830  (instr->ImmException() == kImmExceptionIsDebug)) {
831  const char* message = reinterpret_cast<const char*>(
832  instr->InstructionAtOffset(kDebugMessageOffset));
833  int size = static_cast<int>(kDebugMessageOffset + strlen(message) + 1);
834  return RoundUp(size, kInstrSize) / kInstrSize;
835  }
836  // Same for printf support, see MacroAssembler::CallPrintf().
837  if ((instr->Mask(ExceptionMask) == HLT) &&
838  (instr->ImmException() == kImmExceptionIsPrintf)) {
839  return kPrintfLength / kInstrSize;
840  }
841 #endif
842  if (IsConstantPoolAt(instr)) {
843  return instr->ImmLLiteral();
844  } else {
845  return -1;
846  }
847 }
848 
849 void Assembler::EmitPoolGuard() {
850  // We must generate only one instruction as this is used in scopes that
851  // control the size of the code generated.
852  Emit(BLR | Rn(xzr));
853 }
854 
855 void Assembler::StartBlockVeneerPool() { ++veneer_pool_blocked_nesting_; }
856 
857 void Assembler::EndBlockVeneerPool() {
858  if (--veneer_pool_blocked_nesting_ == 0) {
859  // Check the veneer pool hasn't been blocked for too long.
860  DCHECK(unresolved_branches_.empty() ||
861  (pc_offset() < unresolved_branches_first_limit()));
862  }
863 }

870 void Assembler::blr(const Register& xn) {
871  DCHECK(xn.Is64Bits());
872  // The pattern 'blr xzr' is used as a guard to detect when execution falls
873  // through the constant pool. It should not be emitted.
874  DCHECK_NE(xn, xzr);
875  Emit(BLR | Rn(xn));
876 }

1348 
1349 void Assembler::bti(BranchTargetIdentifier id) {
1350  SystemHint op;
1351  switch (id) {
1352  case BranchTargetIdentifier::kBti:
1353  op = BTI;
1354  break;
1355  case BranchTargetIdentifier::kBtiCall:
1356  op = BTI_c;
1357  break;
1358  case BranchTargetIdentifier::kBtiJump:
1359  op = BTI_j;
1360  break;
1361  case BranchTargetIdentifier::kBtiJumpCall:
1362  op = BTI_jc;
1363  break;
1364  case BranchTargetIdentifier::kNone:
1365  case BranchTargetIdentifier::kPacibsp:
1366  // We always want to generate a BTI instruction here, so disallow
1367  // skipping its generation or generating a PACIBSP instead.
1368  UNREACHABLE();
1369  }
1370  hint(op);
1371 }

1378 void Assembler::stp(const CPURegister& rt, const CPURegister& rt2,
1379  const MemOperand& dst) {
1380  LoadStorePair(rt, rt2, dst, StorePairOpFor(rt, rt2));
1381 
1382 #if defined(V8_OS_WIN)
1383  if (xdata_encoder_ && rt == x29 && rt2 == lr && dst.base().IsSP()) {
1384  xdata_encoder_->onSaveFpLr();
1385  }
1386 #endif
1387 }

1389 void Assembler::ldpsw(const Register& rt, const Register& rt2,
1390  const MemOperand& src) {

1392  LoadStorePair(rt, rt2, src, LDPSW_x);
1393 }
1394 
1395 void Assembler::LoadStorePair(const CPURegister& rt, const CPURegister& rt2,
1396  const MemOperand& addr, LoadStorePairOp op) {
1397  // 'rt' and 'rt2' can only be aliased for stores.
1398  DCHECK(((op & LoadStorePairLBit) == 0) || rt != rt2);
1399  DCHECK(AreSameSizeAndType(rt, rt2));
1400  DCHECK(IsImmLSPair(addr.offset(), CalcLSPairDataSize(op)));
1401  int offset = static_cast<int>(addr.offset());
1402 
1403  Instr memop = op | Rt(rt) | Rt2(rt2) | RnSP(addr.base()) |
1404  ImmLSPair(offset, CalcLSPairDataSize(op));
1405 
1406  Instr addrmodeop;
1407  if (addr.IsImmediateOffset()) {
1408  addrmodeop = LoadStorePairOffsetFixed;
1409  } else {
1410  // Pre-index and post-index modes.
1411  DCHECK_NE(rt, addr.base());
1412  DCHECK_NE(rt2, addr.base());
1413  DCHECK_NE(addr.offset(), 0);
1414  if (addr.IsPreIndex()) {
1415  addrmodeop = LoadStorePairPreIndexFixed;
1416  } else {
1417  DCHECK(addr.IsPostIndex());
1418  addrmodeop = LoadStorePairPostIndexFixed;
1419  }
1420  }
1421  Emit(addrmodeop | memop);
1422 }

1462 void Assembler::ldr_pcrel(const CPURegister& rt, int imm19) {
1463  // The pattern 'ldr xzr, #offset' is used to indicate the beginning of a
1464  // constant pool. It should not be emitted.
1465  DCHECK(!rt.IsZero());
1466  Emit(LoadLiteralOpFor(rt) | ImmLLiteral(imm19) | Rt(rt));
1467 }

1469 Operand Operand::EmbeddedNumber(double number) {
1470  int32_t smi;
1471  if (DoubleToSmiInteger(number, &smi)) {
1472  return Operand(Immediate(Smi::FromInt(smi)));
1473  }
1474  return EmbeddedHeapNumber(number);
1475 }
1476 
1477 Operand Operand::EmbeddedHeapNumber(double number) {
1478  Operand result(0, RelocInfo::FULL_EMBEDDED_OBJECT);
1479  result.heap_number_request_.emplace(number);
1480  DCHECK(result.IsHeapNumberRequest());
1481  return result;
1482 }
1483 
1484 void Assembler::ldr(const CPURegister& rt, const Operand& operand) {
1485  if (operand.IsHeapNumberRequest()) {
1486  BlockPoolsScope no_pool_before_ldr_of_heap_number_request(this);
1487  RequestHeapNumber(operand.heap_number_request());
1488  ldr(rt, operand.immediate_for_heap_number_request());
1489  } else {
1490  ldr(rt, operand.immediate());
1491  }
1492 }
1493 
1494 void Assembler::ldr(const CPURegister& rt, const Immediate& imm) {
1495  BlockPoolsScope no_pool_before_ldr_pcrel_instr(this);
1496  RecordRelocInfo(imm.rmode(), imm.value());
1497  // The load will be patched when the constpool is emitted, patching code
1498  // expect a load literal with offset 0.
1499  ldr_pcrel(rt, 0);
1500 }

1582 #define COMPARE_AND_SWAP_W_X_LIST(V) \
1583  V(cas, CAS) \
1584  V(casa, CASA) \
1585  V(casl, CASL) \
1586  V(casal, CASAL)
1587 
1588 #define DEFINE_ASM_FUNC(FN, OP) \
1589  void Assembler::FN(const Register& rs, const Register& rt, \
1590  const MemOperand& src) { \
1591  DCHECK(IsEnabled(LSE)); \
1592  DCHECK(src.IsImmediateOffset() && (src.offset() == 0)); \
1593  LoadStoreAcquireReleaseOp op = rt.Is64Bits() ? OP##_x : OP##_w; \
1594  Emit(op | Rs(rs) | Rt(rt) | Rt2_mask | RnSP(src.base())); \
1595  }
1596 COMPARE_AND_SWAP_W_X_LIST(DEFINE_ASM_FUNC)
1597 #undef DEFINE_ASM_FUNC
1598 
1599 #define COMPARE_AND_SWAP_W_LIST(V) \
1600  V(casb, CASB) \
1601  V(casab, CASAB) \
1602  V(caslb, CASLB) \
1603  V(casalb, CASALB) \
1604  V(cash, CASH) \
1605  V(casah, CASAH) \
1606  V(caslh, CASLH) \
1607  V(casalh, CASALH)
1608 
1609 #define DEFINE_ASM_FUNC(FN, OP) \
1610  void Assembler::FN(const Register& rs, const Register& rt, \
1611  const MemOperand& src) { \
1612  DCHECK(IsEnabled(LSE)); \
1613  DCHECK(src.IsImmediateOffset() && (src.offset() == 0)); \
1614  Emit(OP | Rs(rs) | Rt(rt) | Rt2_mask | RnSP(src.base())); \
1615  }
1616 COMPARE_AND_SWAP_W_LIST(DEFINE_ASM_FUNC)
1617 #undef DEFINE_ASM_FUNC
1618 
1619 #define COMPARE_AND_SWAP_PAIR_LIST(V) \
1620  V(casp, CASP) \
1621  V(caspa, CASPA) \
1622  V(caspl, CASPL) \
1623  V(caspal, CASPAL)
1624 
1625 #define DEFINE_ASM_FUNC(FN, OP) \
1626  void Assembler::FN(const Register& rs, const Register& rs1, \
1627  const Register& rt, const Register& rt1, \
1628  const MemOperand& src) { \
1629  DCHECK(IsEnabled(LSE)); \
1630  DCHECK(src.IsImmediateOffset() && (src.offset() == 0)); \
1631  DCHECK(AreEven(rs, rt)); \
1632  DCHECK(AreConsecutive(rs, rs1)); \
1633  DCHECK(AreConsecutive(rt, rt1)); \
1634  DCHECK(AreSameFormat(rs, rs1, rt, rt1)); \
1635  LoadStoreAcquireReleaseOp op = rt.Is64Bits() ? OP##_x : OP##_w; \
1636  Emit(op | Rs(rs) | Rt(rt) | Rt2_mask | RnSP(src.base())); \
1637  }
1638 COMPARE_AND_SWAP_PAIR_LIST(DEFINE_ASM_FUNC)
1639 #undef DEFINE_ASM_FUNC
1640 
1641 // These macros generate all the variations of the atomic memory operations,
1642 // e.g. ldadd, ldadda, ldaddb, staddl, etc.
1643 // For a full list of the methods with comments, see the assembler header file.
1644 
1645 #define ATOMIC_MEMORY_SIMPLE_OPERATION_LIST(V, DEF) \
1646  V(DEF, add, LDADD) \
1647  V(DEF, clr, LDCLR) \
1648  V(DEF, eor, LDEOR) \
1649  V(DEF, set, LDSET) \
1650  V(DEF, smax, LDSMAX) \
1651  V(DEF, smin, LDSMIN) \
1652  V(DEF, umax, LDUMAX) \
1653  V(DEF, umin, LDUMIN)
1654 
1655 #define ATOMIC_MEMORY_STORE_MODES(V, NAME, OP) \
1656  V(NAME, OP##_x, OP##_w) \
1657  V(NAME##l, OP##L_x, OP##L_w) \
1658  V(NAME##b, OP##B, OP##B) \
1659  V(NAME##lb, OP##LB, OP##LB) \
1660  V(NAME##h, OP##H, OP##H) \
1661  V(NAME##lh, OP##LH, OP##LH)
1662 
1663 #define ATOMIC_MEMORY_LOAD_MODES(V, NAME, OP) \
1664  ATOMIC_MEMORY_STORE_MODES(V, NAME, OP) \
1665  V(NAME##a, OP##A_x, OP##A_w) \
1666  V(NAME##al, OP##AL_x, OP##AL_w) \
1667  V(NAME##ab, OP##AB, OP##AB) \
1668  V(NAME##alb, OP##ALB, OP##ALB) \
1669  V(NAME##ah, OP##AH, OP##AH) \
1670  V(NAME##alh, OP##ALH, OP##ALH)
1671 
1672 #define DEFINE_ASM_LOAD_FUNC(FN, OP_X, OP_W) \
1673  void Assembler::ld##FN(const Register& rs, const Register& rt, \
1674  const MemOperand& src) { \
1675  DCHECK(IsEnabled(LSE)); \
1676  DCHECK(src.IsImmediateOffset() && (src.offset() == 0)); \
1677  AtomicMemoryOp op = rt.Is64Bits() ? OP_X : OP_W; \
1678  Emit(op | Rs(rs) | Rt(rt) | RnSP(src.base())); \
1679  }
1680 #define DEFINE_ASM_STORE_FUNC(FN, OP_X, OP_W) \
1681  void Assembler::st##FN(const Register& rs, const MemOperand& src) { \
1682  DCHECK(IsEnabled(LSE)); \
1683  ld##FN(rs, AppropriateZeroRegFor(rs), src); \
1684  }
1685 
1686 ATOMIC_MEMORY_SIMPLE_OPERATION_LIST(ATOMIC_MEMORY_LOAD_MODES,
1687  DEFINE_ASM_LOAD_FUNC)
1688 ATOMIC_MEMORY_SIMPLE_OPERATION_LIST(ATOMIC_MEMORY_STORE_MODES,
1689  DEFINE_ASM_STORE_FUNC)
1690 
1691 #define DEFINE_ASM_SWP_FUNC(FN, OP_X, OP_W) \
1692  void Assembler::FN(const Register& rs, const Register& rt, \
1693  const MemOperand& src) { \
1694  DCHECK(IsEnabled(LSE)); \
1695  DCHECK(src.IsImmediateOffset() && (src.offset() == 0)); \
1696  AtomicMemoryOp op = rt.Is64Bits() ? OP_X : OP_W; \
1697  Emit(op | Rs(rs) | Rt(rt) | RnSP(src.base())); \
1698  }
1699 
1700 ATOMIC_MEMORY_LOAD_MODES(DEFINE_ASM_SWP_FUNC, swp, SWP)
1701 
1702 #undef DEFINE_ASM_LOAD_FUNC
1703 #undef DEFINE_ASM_STORE_FUNC
1704 #undef DEFINE_ASM_SWP_FUNC

1706 void Assembler::sdot(const VRegister& vd, const VRegister& vn,
1707  const VRegister& vm) {
1708  DCHECK(IsEnabled(DOTPROD));
1709  DCHECK((vn.Is16B() && vd.Is4S()) || (vn.Is8B() && vd.Is2S()));
1710  DCHECK(AreSameFormat(vn, vm));
1711  Emit(VFormat(vd) | NEON_SDOT | Rm(vm) | Rn(vn) | Rd(vd));
1712 }
1713 
1714 void Assembler::NEON3DifferentL(const VRegister& vd, const VRegister& vn,
1715  const VRegister& vm, NEON3DifferentOp vop) {
1716  DCHECK(AreSameFormat(vn, vm));
1717  DCHECK((vn.Is1H() && vd.Is1S()) || (vn.Is1S() && vd.Is1D()) ||
1718  (vn.Is8B() && vd.Is8H()) || (vn.Is4H() && vd.Is4S()) ||
1719  (vn.Is2S() && vd.Is2D()) || (vn.Is16B() && vd.Is8H()) ||
1720  (vn.Is8H() && vd.Is4S()) || (vn.Is4S() && vd.Is2D()));
1721  Instr format, op = vop;
1722  if (vd.IsScalar()) {
1723  op |= NEON_Q | NEONScalar;
1724  format = SFormat(vn);
1725  } else {
1726  format = VFormat(vn);
1727  }
1728  Emit(format | op | Rm(vm) | Rn(vn) | Rd(vd));
1729 }
1730 
1731 void Assembler::NEON3DifferentW(const VRegister& vd, const VRegister& vn,
1732  const VRegister& vm, NEON3DifferentOp vop) {
1733  DCHECK(AreSameFormat(vd, vn));
1734  DCHECK((vm.Is8B() && vd.Is8H()) || (vm.Is4H() && vd.Is4S()) ||
1735  (vm.Is2S() && vd.Is2D()) || (vm.Is16B() && vd.Is8H()) ||
1736  (vm.Is8H() && vd.Is4S()) || (vm.Is4S() && vd.Is2D()));
1737  Emit(VFormat(vm) | vop | Rm(vm) | Rn(vn) | Rd(vd));
1738 }
1739 
1740 void Assembler::NEON3DifferentHN(const VRegister& vd, const VRegister& vn,
1741  const VRegister& vm, NEON3DifferentOp vop) {
1742  DCHECK(AreSameFormat(vm, vn));
1743  DCHECK((vd.Is8B() && vn.Is8H()) || (vd.Is4H() && vn.Is4S()) ||
1744  (vd.Is2S() && vn.Is2D()) || (vd.Is16B() && vn.Is8H()) ||
1745  (vd.Is8H() && vn.Is4S()) || (vd.Is4S() && vn.Is2D()));
1746  Emit(VFormat(vd) | vop | Rm(vm) | Rn(vn) | Rd(vd));
1747 }

1850 void Assembler::NEONShiftImmediate(const VRegister& vd, const VRegister& vn,
1851  NEONShiftImmediateOp op, int immh_immb) {
1852  DCHECK(AreSameFormat(vd, vn));
1853  Instr q, scalar;
1854  if (vn.IsScalar()) {
1855  q = NEON_Q;
1856  scalar = NEONScalar;
1857  } else {
1858  q = vd.IsD() ? 0 : NEON_Q;
1859  scalar = 0;
1860  }
1861  Emit(q | op | scalar | immh_immb | Rn(vn) | Rd(vd));
1862 }
1863 
1864 void Assembler::NEONShiftLeftImmediate(const VRegister& vd, const VRegister& vn,
1865  int shift, NEONShiftImmediateOp op) {
1866  int laneSizeInBits = vn.LaneSizeInBits();
1867  DCHECK((shift >= 0) && (shift < laneSizeInBits));
1868  NEONShiftImmediate(vd, vn, op, (laneSizeInBits + shift) << 16);
1869 }
1870 
1871 void Assembler::NEONShiftRightImmediate(const VRegister& vd,
1872  const VRegister& vn, int shift,
1873  NEONShiftImmediateOp op) {
1874  int laneSizeInBits = vn.LaneSizeInBits();
1875  DCHECK((shift >= 1) && (shift <= laneSizeInBits));
1876  NEONShiftImmediate(vd, vn, op, ((2 * laneSizeInBits) - shift) << 16);
1877 }
1878 
1879 void Assembler::NEONShiftImmediateL(const VRegister& vd, const VRegister& vn,
1880  int shift, NEONShiftImmediateOp op) {
1881  int laneSizeInBits = vn.LaneSizeInBits();
1882  DCHECK((shift >= 0) && (shift < laneSizeInBits));
1883  int immh_immb = (laneSizeInBits + shift) << 16;
1884 
1885  DCHECK((vn.Is8B() && vd.Is8H()) || (vn.Is4H() && vd.Is4S()) ||
1886  (vn.Is2S() && vd.Is2D()) || (vn.Is16B() && vd.Is8H()) ||
1887  (vn.Is8H() && vd.Is4S()) || (vn.Is4S() && vd.Is2D()));
1888  Instr q;
1889  q = vn.IsD() ? 0 : NEON_Q;
1890  Emit(q | op | immh_immb | Rn(vn) | Rd(vd));
1891 }
1892 
1893 void Assembler::NEONShiftImmediateN(const VRegister& vd, const VRegister& vn,
1894  int shift, NEONShiftImmediateOp op) {
1895  Instr q, scalar;
1896  int laneSizeInBits = vd.LaneSizeInBits();
1897  DCHECK((shift >= 1) && (shift <= laneSizeInBits));
1898  int immh_immb = (2 * laneSizeInBits - shift) << 16;
1899 
1900  if (vn.IsScalar()) {
1901  DCHECK((vd.Is1B() && vn.Is1H()) || (vd.Is1H() && vn.Is1S()) ||
1902  (vd.Is1S() && vn.Is1D()));
1903  q = NEON_Q;
1904  scalar = NEONScalar;
1905  } else {
1906  DCHECK((vd.Is8B() && vn.Is8H()) || (vd.Is4H() && vn.Is4S()) ||
1907  (vd.Is2S() && vn.Is2D()) || (vd.Is16B() && vn.Is8H()) ||
1908  (vd.Is8H() && vn.Is4S()) || (vd.Is4S() && vn.Is2D()));
1909  scalar = 0;
1910  q = vd.IsD() ? 0 : NEON_Q;
1911  }
1912  Emit(q | op | scalar | immh_immb | Rn(vn) | Rd(vd));
1913 }
1914

2146 void Assembler::mov(const Register& rd, const Register& rm) {
2147  // Moves involving the stack pointer are encoded as add immediate with
2148  // second operand of zero. Otherwise, orr with first operand zr is
2149  // used.
2150  if (rd.IsSP() || rm.IsSP()) {
2151  add(rd, rm, 0);
2152  } else {
2153  orr(rd, AppropriateZeroRegFor(rd), rm);
2154  }
2155 }

2157 void Assembler::ins(const VRegister& vd, int vd_index, const Register& rn) {
2158  // We support vd arguments of the form vd.VxT() or vd.T(), where x is the
2159  // number of lanes, and T is b, h, s or d.
2160  int lane_size = vd.LaneSizeInBytes();
2161  NEONFormatField format;
2162  switch (lane_size) {
2163  case 1:
2164  format = NEON_16B;
2165  DCHECK(rn.IsW());
2166  break;
2167  case 2:
2168  format = NEON_8H;
2169  DCHECK(rn.IsW());
2170  break;
2171  case 4:
2172  format = NEON_4S;
2173  DCHECK(rn.IsW());
2174  break;
2175  default:
2176  DCHECK_EQ(lane_size, 8);
2177  DCHECK(rn.IsX());
2178  format = NEON_2D;
2179  break;
2180  }
2181 
2182  DCHECK((0 <= vd_index) &&
2183  (vd_index < LaneCountFromFormat(static_cast<VectorFormat>(format))));
2184  Emit(NEON_INS_GENERAL | ImmNEON5(format, vd_index) | Rn(rn) | Rd(vd));
2185 }

2192 void Assembler::smov(const Register& rd, const VRegister& vn, int vn_index) {
2193  // We support vn arguments of the form vn.VxT() or vn.T(), where x is the
2194  // number of lanes, and T is b, h, s.
2195  int lane_size = vn.LaneSizeInBytes();
2196  NEONFormatField format;
2197  Instr q = 0;
2198  switch (lane_size) {
2199  case 1:
2200  format = NEON_16B;
2201  break;
2202  case 2:
2203  format = NEON_8H;
2204  break;
2205  default:
2206  DCHECK_EQ(lane_size, 4);
2207  DCHECK(rd.IsX());
2208  format = NEON_4S;
2209  break;
2210  }
2211  q = rd.IsW() ? 0 : NEON_Q;
2212  DCHECK((0 <= vn_index) &&
2213  (vn_index < LaneCountFromFormat(static_cast<VectorFormat>(format))));
2214  Emit(q | NEON_SMOV | ImmNEON5(format, vn_index) | Rn(vn) | Rd(rd));
2215 }

2308 void Assembler::NEONAcrossLanes(const VRegister& vd, const VRegister& vn,
2309  NEONAcrossLanesOp op) {
2310  DCHECK((vn.Is8B() && vd.Is1B()) || (vn.Is16B() && vd.Is1B()) ||
2311  (vn.Is4H() && vd.Is1H()) || (vn.Is8H() && vd.Is1H()) ||
2312  (vn.Is4S() && vd.Is1S()));
2313  if ((op & NEONAcrossLanesFPFMask) == NEONAcrossLanesFPFixed) {
2314  Emit(FPFormat(vn) | op | Rn(vn) | Rd(vd));
2315  } else {
2316  Emit(VFormat(vn) | op | Rn(vn) | Rd(vd));
2317  }
2318 }

2320 #define NEON_ACROSSLANES_LIST(V) \
2321  V(fmaxv, NEON_FMAXV, vd.Is1S()) \
2322  V(fminv, NEON_FMINV, vd.Is1S()) \
2323  V(fmaxnmv, NEON_FMAXNMV, vd.Is1S()) \
2324  V(fminnmv, NEON_FMINNMV, vd.Is1S()) \
2325  V(addv, NEON_ADDV, true) \
2326  V(smaxv, NEON_SMAXV, true) \
2327  V(sminv, NEON_SMINV, true) \
2328  V(umaxv, NEON_UMAXV, true) \
2329  V(uminv, NEON_UMINV, true)
2330 
2331 #define DEFINE_ASM_FUNC(FN, OP, AS) \
2332  void Assembler::FN(const VRegister& vd, const VRegister& vn) { \
2333  DCHECK(AS); \
2334  NEONAcrossLanes(vd, vn, OP); \
2335  }
2336 NEON_ACROSSLANES_LIST(DEFINE_ASM_FUNC)
2337 #undef DEFINE_ASM_FUNC

2343 void Assembler::umov(const Register& rd, const VRegister& vn, int vn_index) {
2344  // We support vn arguments of the form vn.VxT() or vn.T(), where x is the
2345  // number of lanes, and T is b, h, s or d.
2346  int lane_size = vn.LaneSizeInBytes();
2347  NEONFormatField format;
2348  Instr q = 0;
2349  switch (lane_size) {
2350  case 1:
2351  format = NEON_16B;
2352  DCHECK(rd.IsW());
2353  break;
2354  case 2:
2355  format = NEON_8H;
2356  DCHECK(rd.IsW());
2357  break;
2358  case 4:
2359  format = NEON_4S;
2360  DCHECK(rd.IsW());
2361  break;
2362  default:
2363  DCHECK_EQ(lane_size, 8);
2364  DCHECK(rd.IsX());
2365  format = NEON_2D;
2366  q = NEON_Q;
2367  break;
2368  }
2369 
2370  DCHECK((0 <= vn_index) &&
2371  (vn_index < LaneCountFromFormat(static_cast<VectorFormat>(format))));
2372  Emit(q | NEON_UMOV | ImmNEON5(format, vn_index) | Rn(vn) | Rd(rd));
2373 }

2387 void Assembler::ins(const VRegister& vd, int vd_index, const VRegister& vn,
2388  int vn_index) {
2389  DCHECK(AreSameFormat(vd, vn));
2390  // We support vd arguments of the form vd.VxT() or vd.T(), where x is the
2391  // number of lanes, and T is b, h, s or d.
2392  int lane_size = vd.LaneSizeInBytes();
2393  NEONFormatField format;
2394  switch (lane_size) {
2395  case 1:
2396  format = NEON_16B;
2397  break;
2398  case 2:
2399  format = NEON_8H;
2400  break;
2401  case 4:
2402  format = NEON_4S;
2403  break;
2404  default:
2405  DCHECK_EQ(lane_size, 8);
2406  format = NEON_2D;
2407  break;
2408  }
2409 
2410  DCHECK((0 <= vd_index) &&
2411  (vd_index < LaneCountFromFormat(static_cast<VectorFormat>(format))));
2412  DCHECK((0 <= vn_index) &&
2413  (vn_index < LaneCountFromFormat(static_cast<VectorFormat>(format))));
2414  Emit(NEON_INS_ELEMENT | ImmNEON5(format, vd_index) |
2415  ImmNEON4(format, vn_index) | Rn(vn) | Rd(vd));
2416 }

2513 void Assembler::hint(SystemHint code) { Emit(HINT | ImmHint(code) | Rt(xzr)); }

2515 // NEON structure loads and stores.
2516 Instr Assembler::LoadStoreStructAddrModeField(const MemOperand& addr) {
2517  Instr addr_field = RnSP(addr.base());
2518 
2519  if (addr.IsPostIndex()) {
2520  static_assert(NEONLoadStoreMultiStructPostIndex ==
2521  static_cast<NEONLoadStoreMultiStructPostIndexOp>(
2522  NEONLoadStoreSingleStructPostIndex),
2523  "Opcodes must match for NEON post index memop.");
2524 
2525  addr_field |= NEONLoadStoreMultiStructPostIndex;
2526  if (addr.offset() == 0) {
2527  addr_field |= RmNot31(addr.regoffset());
2528  } else {
2529  // The immediate post index addressing mode is indicated by rm = 31.
2530  // The immediate is implied by the number of vector registers used.
2531  addr_field |= (0x1F << Rm_offset);
2532  }
2533  } else {
2534  DCHECK(addr.IsImmediateOffset() && (addr.offset() == 0));
2535  }
2536  return addr_field;
2537 }
2538 
2539 void Assembler::LoadStoreStructVerify(const VRegister& vt,
2540  const MemOperand& addr, Instr op) {
2541 #ifdef DEBUG
2542  // Assert that addressing mode is either offset (with immediate 0), post
2543  // index by immediate of the size of the register list, or post index by a
2544  // value in a core register.
2545  if (addr.IsImmediateOffset()) {
2546  DCHECK_EQ(addr.offset(), 0);
2547  } else {
2548  int offset = vt.SizeInBytes();
2549  switch (op) {
2550  case NEON_LD1_1v:
2551  case NEON_ST1_1v:
2552  offset *= 1;
2553  break;
2554  case NEONLoadStoreSingleStructLoad1:
2555  case NEONLoadStoreSingleStructStore1:
2556  case NEON_LD1R:
2557  offset = (offset / vt.LaneCount()) * 1;
2558  break;
2559 
2560  case NEON_LD1_2v:
2561  case NEON_ST1_2v:
2562  case NEON_LD2:
2563  case NEON_ST2:
2564  offset *= 2;
2565  break;
2566  case NEONLoadStoreSingleStructLoad2:
2567  case NEONLoadStoreSingleStructStore2:
2568  case NEON_LD2R:
2569  offset = (offset / vt.LaneCount()) * 2;
2570  break;
2571 
2572  case NEON_LD1_3v:
2573  case NEON_ST1_3v:
2574  case NEON_LD3:
2575  case NEON_ST3:
2576  offset *= 3;
2577  break;
2578  case NEONLoadStoreSingleStructLoad3:
2579  case NEONLoadStoreSingleStructStore3:
2580  case NEON_LD3R:
2581  offset = (offset / vt.LaneCount()) * 3;
2582  break;
2583 
2584  case NEON_LD1_4v:
2585  case NEON_ST1_4v:
2586  case NEON_LD4:
2587  case NEON_ST4:
2588  offset *= 4;
2589  break;
2590  case NEONLoadStoreSingleStructLoad4:
2591  case NEONLoadStoreSingleStructStore4:
2592  case NEON_LD4R:
2593  offset = (offset / vt.LaneCount()) * 4;
2594  break;
2595  default:
2596  UNREACHABLE();
2597  }
2598  DCHECK(addr.regoffset() != NoReg || addr.offset() == offset);
2599  }
2600 #else
2601  USE(vt);
2602  USE(addr);
2603  USE(op);
2604 #endif
2605 }
2606 
2607 void Assembler::LoadStoreStruct(const VRegister& vt, const MemOperand& addr,
2608  NEONLoadStoreMultiStructOp op) {
2609  LoadStoreStructVerify(vt, addr, op);
2610  DCHECK(vt.IsVector() || vt.Is1D());
2611  Emit(op | LoadStoreStructAddrModeField(addr) | LSVFormat(vt) | Rt(vt));
2612 }
2613 
2614 void Assembler::LoadStoreStructSingleAllLanes(const VRegister& vt,
2615  const MemOperand& addr,
2616  NEONLoadStoreSingleStructOp op) {
2617  LoadStoreStructVerify(vt, addr, op);
2618  Emit(op | LoadStoreStructAddrModeField(addr) | LSVFormat(vt) | Rt(vt));
2619 }

2824 
2825 void Assembler::LoadStoreStructSingle(const VRegister& vt, uint32_t lane,
2826  const MemOperand& addr,
2827  NEONLoadStoreSingleStructOp op) {
2828  LoadStoreStructVerify(vt, addr, op);
2829 
2830  // We support vt arguments of the form vt.VxT() or vt.T(), where x is the
2831  // number of lanes, and T is b, h, s or d.
2832  unsigned lane_size = vt.LaneSizeInBytes();
2833  DCHECK_LT(lane, kQRegSize / lane_size);
2834 
2835  // Lane size is encoded in the opcode field. Lane index is encoded in the Q,
2836  // S and size fields.
2837  lane *= lane_size;
2838 
2839  // Encodings for S[0]/D[0] and S[2]/D[1] are distinguished using the least-
2840  // significant bit of the size field, so we increment lane here to account for
2841  // that.
2842  if (lane_size == 8) lane++;
2843 
2844  Instr size = (lane << NEONLSSize_offset) & NEONLSSize_mask;
2845  Instr s = (lane << (NEONS_offset - 2)) & NEONS_mask;
2846  Instr q = (lane << (NEONQ_offset - 3)) & NEONQ_mask;
2847 
2848  Instr instr = op;
2849  switch (lane_size) {
2850  case 1:
2851  instr |= NEONLoadStoreSingle_b;
2852  break;
2853  case 2:
2854  instr |= NEONLoadStoreSingle_h;
2855  break;
2856  case 4:
2857  instr |= NEONLoadStoreSingle_s;
2858  break;
2859  default:
2860  DCHECK_EQ(lane_size, 8U);
2861  instr |= NEONLoadStoreSingle_d;
2862  }
2863 
2864  Emit(instr | LoadStoreStructAddrModeField(addr) | q | size | s | Rt(vt));
2865 }
2866

2893 void Assembler::fmov(const VRegister& vd, double imm) {
2894  if (vd.IsScalar()) {
2895  DCHECK(vd.Is1D());
2896  Emit(FMOV_d_imm | Rd(vd) | ImmFP(imm));
2897  } else {
2898  DCHECK(vd.Is2D());
2899  Instr op = NEONModifiedImmediate_MOVI | NEONModifiedImmediateOpBit;
2900  Emit(NEON_Q | op | ImmNEONFP(imm) | NEONCmode(0xF) | Rd(vd));
2901  }
2902 }
2903 
2904 void Assembler::fmov(const VRegister& vd, float imm) {
2905  if (vd.IsScalar()) {
2906  DCHECK(vd.Is1S());
2907  Emit(FMOV_s_imm | Rd(vd) | ImmFP(imm));
2908  } else {
2909  DCHECK(vd.Is2S() || vd.Is4S());
2910  Instr op = NEONModifiedImmediate_MOVI;
2911  Instr q = vd.Is4S() ? NEON_Q : 0;
2912  Emit(q | op | ImmNEONFP(imm) | NEONCmode(0xF) | Rd(vd));
2913  }
2914 }

2977 void Assembler::fcmp(const VRegister& fn, double value) {
2978  USE(value);
2979  // Although the fcmp instruction can strictly only take an immediate value of
2980  // +0.0, we don't need to check for -0.0 because the sign of 0.0 doesn't
2981  // affect the result of the comparison.
2982  DCHECK_EQ(value, 0.0);
2983  Emit(FPType(fn) | FCMP_zero | Rn(fn));
2984 }

3005  Instr op) {
3006  if (vn.IsScalar()) {
3007  DCHECK((vd.Is1S() && vn.Is1S()) || (vd.Is1D() && vn.Is1D()));

3013 void Assembler::fcvt(const VRegister& vd, const VRegister& vn) {
3014  FPDataProcessing1SourceOp op;
3015  if (vd.Is1D()) {
3016  DCHECK(vn.Is1S() || vn.Is1H());
3017  op = vn.Is1S() ? FCVT_ds : FCVT_dh;
3018  } else if (vd.Is1S()) {
3019  DCHECK(vn.Is1D() || vn.Is1H());
3020  op = vn.Is1D() ? FCVT_sd : FCVT_sh;
3021  } else {
3022  DCHECK(vd.Is1H());
3023  DCHECK(vn.Is1D() || vn.Is1S());
3024  op = vn.Is1D() ? FCVT_hd : FCVT_hs;
3025  }
3026  FPDataProcessing1Source(vd, vn, op);
3027 }

3095 void Assembler::scvtf(const VRegister& vd, const VRegister& vn, int fbits) {
3096  DCHECK_GE(fbits, 0);
3097  if (fbits == 0) {
3098  NEONFP2RegMisc(vd, vn, NEON_SCVTF, 0.0);
3099  } else {
3100  DCHECK(vd.Is1D() || vd.Is1S() || vd.Is2D() || vd.Is2S() || vd.Is4S());
3101  NEONShiftRightImmediate(vd, vn, fbits, NEON_SCVTF_imm);
3102  }
3103 }

3106  DCHECK_GE(fbits, 0);
3107  if (fbits == 0) {
3108  NEONFP2RegMisc(vd, vn, NEON_UCVTF, 0.0);
3109  } else {
3110  DCHECK(vd.Is1D() || vd.Is1S() || vd.Is2D() || vd.Is2S() || vd.Is4S());
3111  NEONShiftRightImmediate(vd, vn, fbits, NEON_UCVTF_imm);
3112  }
3113 }

3115 void Assembler::scvtf(const VRegister& vd, const Register& rn, int fbits) {
3116  DCHECK_GE(fbits, 0);
3117  if (fbits == 0) {
3118  Emit(SF(rn) | FPType(vd) | SCVTF | Rn(rn) | Rd(vd));
3119  } else {
3120  Emit(SF(rn) | FPType(vd) | SCVTF_fixed | FPScale(64 - fbits) | Rn(rn) |
3121  Rd(vd));
3122  }
3123 }
3124 
3125 void Assembler::ucvtf(const VRegister& fd, const Register& rn, int fbits) {
3126  DCHECK_GE(fbits, 0);
3127  if (fbits == 0) {
3128  Emit(SF(rn) | FPType(fd) | UCVTF | Rn(rn) | Rd(fd));
3129  } else {
3130  Emit(SF(rn) | FPType(fd) | UCVTF_fixed | FPScale(64 - fbits) | Rn(rn) |
3131  Rd(fd));
3132  }
3133 }

3135 void Assembler::NEON3Same(const VRegister& vd, const VRegister& vn,
3136  const VRegister& vm, NEON3SameOp vop) {
3137  DCHECK(AreSameFormat(vd, vn, vm));
3138  DCHECK(vd.IsVector() || !vd.IsQ());
3139 
3140  Instr format, op = vop;
3141  if (vd.IsScalar()) {
3142  op |= NEON_Q | NEONScalar;
3143  format = SFormat(vd);
3144  } else {
3145  format = VFormat(vd);
3146  }
3147 
3148  Emit(format | op | Rm(vm) | Rn(vn) | Rd(vd));
3149 }

3155  op |= NEON_sz;
3156  op ^= NEON3SameHPMask;
3157  }
3158  Emit(FPFormat(vd) | op | Rm(vm) | Rn(vn) | Rd(vd));

3508 void Assembler::movi(const VRegister& vd, const uint64_t imm, Shift shift,
3509  const int shift_amount) {
3510  DCHECK((shift == LSL) || (shift == MSL));
3511  if (vd.Is2D() || vd.Is1D()) {
3512  DCHECK_EQ(shift_amount, 0);
3513  int imm8 = 0;
3514  for (int i = 0; i < 8; ++i) {
3515  int byte = (imm >> (i * 8)) & 0xFF;
3516  DCHECK((byte == 0) || (byte == 0xFF));
3517  if (byte == 0xFF) {
3518  imm8 |= (1 << i);
3519  }
3520  }
3521  Instr q = vd.Is2D() ? NEON_Q : 0;
3522  Emit(q | NEONModImmOp(1) | NEONModifiedImmediate_MOVI |
3523  ImmNEONabcdefgh(imm8) | NEONCmode(0xE) | Rd(vd));
3524  } else if (shift == LSL) {
3525  DCHECK(is_uint8(imm));
3526  NEONModifiedImmShiftLsl(vd, static_cast<int>(imm), shift_amount,
3527  NEONModifiedImmediate_MOVI);
3528  } else {
3529  DCHECK(is_uint8(imm));
3530  NEONModifiedImmShiftMsl(vd, static_cast<int>(imm), shift_amount,
3531  NEONModifiedImmediate_MOVI);
3532  }
3533 }

3536  DCHECK(AreSameFormat(vd, vn));
3537  if (vd.IsD()) {
3538  not_(vd.V8B(), vn.V8B());
3539  } else {
3540  DCHECK(vd.IsQ());
3541  not_(vd.V16B(), vn.V16B());
3542  }
3543 }
3544 
3545 void Assembler::mvni(const VRegister& vd, const int imm8, Shift shift,
3546  const int shift_amount) {
3547  DCHECK((shift == LSL) || (shift == MSL));
3548  if (shift == LSL) {
3549  NEONModifiedImmShiftLsl(vd, imm8, shift_amount, NEONModifiedImmediate_MVNI);
3550  } else {
3551  NEONModifiedImmShiftMsl(vd, imm8, shift_amount, NEONModifiedImmediate_MVNI);
3552  }
3553 }
3554 
3555 void Assembler::NEONFPByElement(const VRegister& vd, const VRegister& vn,
3556  const VRegister& vm, int vm_index,
3557  NEONByIndexedElementOp vop) {
3558  DCHECK(AreSameFormat(vd, vn));
3559  DCHECK((vd.Is2S() && vm.Is1S()) || (vd.Is4S() && vm.Is1S()) ||
3560  (vd.Is1S() && vm.Is1S()) || (vd.Is2D() && vm.Is1D()) ||
3561  (vd.Is1D() && vm.Is1D()));
3562  DCHECK((vm.Is1S() && (vm_index < 4)) || (vm.Is1D() && (vm_index < 2)));
3563 
3564  Instr op = vop;
3565  int index_num_bits = vm.Is1S() ? 2 : 1;
3566  if (vd.IsScalar()) {
3567  op |= NEON_Q | NEONScalar;
3568  }
3569 
3570  Emit(FPFormat(vd) | op | ImmNEONHLM(vm_index, index_num_bits) | Rm(vm) |
3571  Rn(vn) | Rd(vd));
3572 }

3574 void Assembler::NEONByElement(const VRegister& vd, const VRegister& vn,
3575  const VRegister& vm, int vm_index,
3576  NEONByIndexedElementOp vop) {
3577  DCHECK(AreSameFormat(vd, vn));
3578  DCHECK((vd.Is4H() && vm.Is1H()) || (vd.Is8H() && vm.Is1H()) ||
3579  (vd.Is1H() && vm.Is1H()) || (vd.Is2S() && vm.Is1S()) ||
3580  (vd.Is4S() && vm.Is1S()) || (vd.Is1S() && vm.Is1S()));
3581  DCHECK((vm.Is1H() && (vm.code() < 16) && (vm_index < 8)) ||
3582  (vm.Is1S() && (vm_index < 4)));
3583 
3584  Instr format, op = vop;
3585  int index_num_bits = vm.Is1H() ? 3 : 2;
3586  if (vd.IsScalar()) {
3587  op |= NEONScalar | NEON_Q;
3588  format = SFormat(vn);
3589  } else {
3590  format = VFormat(vn);
3591  }
3592  Emit(format | op | ImmNEONHLM(vm_index, index_num_bits) | Rm(vm) | Rn(vn) |
3593  Rd(vd));
3594 }

3784 void Assembler::dup(const VRegister& vd, const VRegister& vn, int vn_index) {
3785  Instr q, scalar;
3786 
3787  // We support vn arguments of the form vn.VxT() or vn.T(), where x is the
3788  // number of lanes, and T is b, h, s or d.
3789  int lane_size = vn.LaneSizeInBytes();
3790  NEONFormatField format;
3791  switch (lane_size) {
3792  case 1:
3793  format = NEON_16B;
3794  break;
3795  case 2:
3796  format = NEON_8H;
3797  break;
3798  case 4:
3799  format = NEON_4S;
3800  break;
3801  default:
3802  DCHECK_EQ(lane_size, 8);
3803  format = NEON_2D;
3804  break;
3805  }
3806 
3807  if (vd.IsScalar()) {
3808  q = NEON_Q;
3809  scalar = NEONScalar;
3810  } else {
3811  DCHECK(!vd.Is1D());
3812  q = vd.IsD() ? 0 : NEON_Q;
3813  scalar = 0;
3814  }
3815  Emit(q | scalar | NEON_DUP_ELEMENT | ImmNEON5(format, vn_index) | Rn(vn) |
3816  Rd(vd));
3817 }
3818 
3819 void Assembler::dcptr(Label* label) {
3820  BlockPoolsScope no_pool_inbetween(this);
3821  RecordRelocInfo(RelocInfo::INTERNAL_REFERENCE);
3822  if (label->is_bound()) {
3823  // The label is bound, so it does not need to be updated and the internal
3824  // reference should be emitted.
3825  //
3826  // In this case, label->pos() returns the offset of the label from the
3827  // start of the buffer.
3828  internal_reference_positions_.push_back(pc_offset());
3829  dc64(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(buffer_start_ + label->pos()));
3830  } else {
3831  int32_t offset;
3832  if (label->is_linked()) {
3833  // The label is linked, so the internal reference should be added
3834  // onto the end of the label's link chain.
3835  //
3836  // In this case, label->pos() returns the offset of the last linked
3837  // instruction from the start of the buffer.
3838  offset = label->pos() - pc_offset();
3839  DCHECK_NE(offset, kStartOfLabelLinkChain);
3840  } else {
3841  // The label is unused, so it now becomes linked and the internal
3842  // reference is at the start of the new link chain.
3843  offset = kStartOfLabelLinkChain;
3844  }
3845  // The instruction at pc is now the last link in the label's chain.
3846  label->link_to(pc_offset());
3847 
3848  // Traditionally the offset to the previous instruction in the chain is
3849  // encoded in the instruction payload (e.g. branch range) but internal
3850  // references are not instructions so while unbound they are encoded as
3851  // two consecutive brk instructions. The two 16-bit immediates are used
3852  // to encode the offset.
3853  offset >>= kInstrSizeLog2;
3854  DCHECK(is_int32(offset));
3855  uint32_t high16 = unsigned_bitextract_32(31, 16, offset);
3856  uint32_t low16 = unsigned_bitextract_32(15, 0, offset);
3857 
3858  brk(high16);
3859  brk(low16);
3860  }
3861 }
3862 
3863 // Below, a difference in case for the same letter indicates a
3864 // negated bit. If b is 1, then B is 0.
3865 uint32_t Assembler::FPToImm8(double imm) {
3866  uint64_t bits = base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(imm);
3867  DCHECK(IsImmFP64(bits));
3868  // bits: aBbb.bbbb.bbcd.efgh.0000.0000.0000.0000
3869  // 0000.0000.0000.0000.0000.0000.0000.0000
3870  // bit7: a000.0000
3871  uint64_t bit7 = ((bits >> 63) & 0x1) << 7;
3872  // bit6: 0b00.0000
3873  uint64_t bit6 = ((bits >> 61) & 0x1) << 6;
3874  // bit5_to_0: 00cd.efgh
3875  uint64_t bit5_to_0 = (bits >> 48) & 0x3F;
3876 
3877  return static_cast<uint32_t>(bit7 | bit6 | bit5_to_0);
3878 }
3879 
3880 Instr Assembler::ImmFP(double imm) { return FPToImm8(imm) << ImmFP_offset; }
3881 Instr Assembler::ImmNEONFP(double imm) {
3882  return ImmNEONabcdefgh(FPToImm8(imm));
3883 }
3884 
3885 // InstructionStream generation helpers.
3886 void Assembler::MoveWide(const Register& rd, uint64_t imm, int shift,
3887  MoveWideImmediateOp mov_op) {
3888  // Ignore the top 32 bits of an immediate if we're moving to a W register.
3889  if (rd.Is32Bits()) {
3890  // Check that the top 32 bits are zero (a positive 32-bit number) or top
3891  // 33 bits are one (a negative 32-bit number, sign extended to 64 bits).
3892  DCHECK(((imm >> kWRegSizeInBits) == 0) ||
3893  ((imm >> (kWRegSizeInBits - 1)) == 0x1FFFFFFFF));
3894  imm &= kWRegMask;
3895  }
3896 
3897  if (shift >= 0) {
3898  // Explicit shift specified.
3899  DCHECK((shift == 0) || (shift == 16) || (shift == 32) || (shift == 48));
3900  DCHECK(rd.Is64Bits() || (shift == 0) || (shift == 16));
3901  shift /= 16;
3902  } else {
3903  // Calculate a new immediate and shift combination to encode the immediate
3904  // argument.
3905  shift = 0;
3906  if ((imm & ~0xFFFFULL) == 0) {
3907  // Nothing to do.
3908  } else if ((imm & ~(0xFFFFULL << 16)) == 0) {
3909  imm >>= 16;
3910  shift = 1;
3911  } else if ((imm & ~(0xFFFFULL << 32)) == 0) {
3912  DCHECK(rd.Is64Bits());
3913  imm >>= 32;
3914  shift = 2;
3915  } else if ((imm & ~(0xFFFFULL << 48)) == 0) {
3916  DCHECK(rd.Is64Bits());
3917  imm >>= 48;
3918  shift = 3;
3919  }
3920  }
3921 
3922  DCHECK(is_uint16(imm));
3923 
3924  Emit(SF(rd) | MoveWideImmediateFixed | mov_op | Rd(rd) |
3925  ImmMoveWide(static_cast<int>(imm)) | ShiftMoveWide(shift));
3926 }
3927 
3928 void Assembler::AddSub(const Register& rd, const Register& rn,
3929  const Operand& operand, FlagsUpdate S, AddSubOp op) {
3930  DCHECK_EQ(rd.SizeInBits(), rn.SizeInBits());
3931  DCHECK(!operand.NeedsRelocation(this));
3932  if (operand.IsImmediate()) {
3933  int64_t immediate = operand.ImmediateValue();
3934  DCHECK(IsImmAddSub(immediate));
3935  Instr dest_reg = (S == SetFlags) ? Rd(rd) : RdSP(rd);
3936  Emit(SF(rd) | AddSubImmediateFixed | op | Flags(S) |
3937  ImmAddSub(static_cast<int>(immediate)) | dest_reg | RnSP(rn));
3938  } else if (operand.IsShiftedRegister()) {
3939  DCHECK_EQ(operand.reg().SizeInBits(), rd.SizeInBits());
3940  DCHECK_NE(operand.shift(), ROR);
3941 
3942  // For instructions of the form:
3943  // add/sub wsp, <Wn>, <Wm> [, LSL #0-3 ]
3944  // add/sub <Wd>, wsp, <Wm> [, LSL #0-3 ]
3945  // add/sub wsp, wsp, <Wm> [, LSL #0-3 ]
3946  // adds/subs <Wd>, wsp, <Wm> [, LSL #0-3 ]
3947  // or their 64-bit register equivalents, convert the operand from shifted to
3948  // extended register mode, and emit an add/sub extended instruction.
3949  if (rn.IsSP() || rd.IsSP()) {
3950  DCHECK(!(rd.IsSP() && (S == SetFlags)));
3951  DataProcExtendedRegister(rd, rn, operand.ToExtendedRegister(), S,
3952  AddSubExtendedFixed | op);
3953  } else {
3954  DataProcShiftedRegister(rd, rn, operand, S, AddSubShiftedFixed | op);
3955  }
3956  } else {
3957  DCHECK(operand.IsExtendedRegister());
3958  DataProcExtendedRegister(rd, rn, operand, S, AddSubExtendedFixed | op);
3959  }
3960 }
3961 
3962 void Assembler::AddSubWithCarry(const Register& rd, const Register& rn,
3963  const Operand& operand, FlagsUpdate S,
3964  AddSubWithCarryOp op) {
3965  DCHECK_EQ(rd.SizeInBits(), rn.SizeInBits());
3966  DCHECK_EQ(rd.SizeInBits(), operand.reg().SizeInBits());
3967  DCHECK(operand.IsShiftedRegister() && (operand.shift_amount() == 0));
3968  DCHECK(!operand.NeedsRelocation(this));
3969  Emit(SF(rd) | op | Flags(S) | Rm(operand.reg()) | Rn(rn) | Rd(rd));
3970 }

3975 }

3977 void Assembler::brk(int code) {

3982 void Assembler::EmitStringData(const char* string) {
3983  size_t len = strlen(string) + 1;
3984  DCHECK_LE(RoundUp(len, kInstrSize), static_cast<size_t>(kGap));
3985  EmitData(string, static_cast<int>(len));
3986  // Pad with nullptr characters until pc_ is aligned.
3987  const char pad[] = {'\0', '\0', '\0', '\0'};
3988  static_assert(sizeof(pad) == kInstrSize,
3989  "Size of padding must match instruction size.");
3990  EmitData(pad, RoundUp(pc_offset(), kInstrSize) - pc_offset());
3991 }

3993 void Assembler::WriteJumpTableEntry(Label* label, int table_pos) {
3994  if constexpr (V8_JUMP_TABLE_INFO_BOOL) {
3995  jump_table_info_writer_.Add(pc_offset(), label->pos());
3996  }
3997  dc32(label->pos() - table_pos);
3998 }
3999 
4000 int Assembler::WriteJumpTableInfos() {
4001  if constexpr (!V8_JUMP_TABLE_INFO_BOOL) return 0;
4002  if (jump_table_info_writer_.entry_count() == 0) return 0;
4003  int offset = pc_offset();
4004  jump_table_info_writer_.Emit(this);
4005  int size = pc_offset() - offset;
4006  DCHECK_EQ(size, jump_table_info_writer_.size_in_bytes());
4007  return size;
4008 }

4010 void Assembler::debug(const char* message, uint32_t code, Instr params) {
4011  if (options().enable_simulator_code) {
4012  size_t size_of_debug_sequence =
4013  4 * kInstrSize + RoundUp<kInstrSize>(strlen(message) + 1);
4014 
4015  // The arguments to the debug marker need to be contiguous in memory, so
4016  // make sure we don't try to emit pools.
4017  BlockPoolsScope scope(this, size_of_debug_sequence);
4018 
4019  Label start;
4020  bind(&start);
4021 
4022  // Refer to instructions-arm64.h for a description of the marker and its
4023  // arguments.
4024  hlt(kImmExceptionIsDebug);
4025  DCHECK_EQ(SizeOfCodeGeneratedSince(&start), kDebugCodeOffset);
4026  dc32(code);
4027  DCHECK_EQ(SizeOfCodeGeneratedSince(&start), kDebugParamsOffset);
4028  dc32(params);
4029  DCHECK_EQ(SizeOfCodeGeneratedSince(&start), kDebugMessageOffset);
4030  EmitStringData(message);
4031  hlt(kImmExceptionIsUnreachable);
4032  DCHECK_EQ(SizeOfCodeGeneratedSince(&start), size_of_debug_sequence);
4033 
4034  return;
4035  }
4036 
4037  if (params & BREAK) {
4038  brk(0);
4039  }
4040 }
4041 
4042 void Assembler::Logical(const Register& rd, const Register& rn,
4043  const Operand& operand, LogicalOp op) {
4044  DCHECK(rd.SizeInBits() == rn.SizeInBits());
4045  DCHECK(!operand.NeedsRelocation(this));
4046  if (operand.IsImmediate()) {
4047  int64_t immediate = operand.ImmediateValue();
4048  unsigned reg_size = rd.SizeInBits();
4049 
4050  DCHECK_NE(immediate, 0);
4051  DCHECK_NE(immediate, -1);
4052  DCHECK(rd.Is64Bits() || is_uint32(immediate));
4053 
4054  // If the operation is NOT, invert the operation and immediate.
4055  if ((op & NOT) == NOT) {
4056  op = static_cast<LogicalOp>(op & ~NOT);
4057  immediate = rd.Is64Bits() ? ~immediate : (~immediate & kWRegMask);
4058  }
4059 
4060  unsigned n, imm_s, imm_r;
4061  if (IsImmLogical(immediate, reg_size, &n, &imm_s, &imm_r)) {
4062  // Immediate can be encoded in the instruction.
4063  LogicalImmediate(rd, rn, n, imm_s, imm_r, op);
4064  } else {
4065  // This case is handled in the macro assembler.
4066  UNREACHABLE();
4067  }
4068  } else {
4069  DCHECK(operand.IsShiftedRegister());
4070  DCHECK(operand.reg().SizeInBits() == rd.SizeInBits());
4071  Instr dp_op = static_cast<Instr>(op | LogicalShiftedFixed);
4072  DataProcShiftedRegister(rd, rn, operand, LeaveFlags, dp_op);
4073  }
4074 }
4075 
4076 void Assembler::LogicalImmediate(const Register& rd, const Register& rn,
4077  unsigned n, unsigned imm_s, unsigned imm_r,
4078  LogicalOp op) {
4079  unsigned reg_size = rd.SizeInBits();
4080  Instr dest_reg = (op == ANDS) ? Rd(rd) : RdSP(rd);
4081  Emit(SF(rd) | LogicalImmediateFixed | op | BitN(n, reg_size) |
4082  ImmSetBits(imm_s, reg_size) | ImmRotate(imm_r, reg_size) | dest_reg |
4083  Rn(rn));
4084 }
4085 
4086 void Assembler::ConditionalCompare(const Register& rn, const Operand& operand,
4087  StatusFlags nzcv, Condition cond,
4088  ConditionalCompareOp op) {
4089  Instr ccmpop;
4090  DCHECK(!operand.NeedsRelocation(this));
4091  if (operand.IsImmediate()) {
4092  int64_t immediate = operand.ImmediateValue();
4093  DCHECK(IsImmConditionalCompare(immediate));
4094  ccmpop = ConditionalCompareImmediateFixed | op |
4095  ImmCondCmp(static_cast<unsigned>(immediate));
4096  } else {
4097  DCHECK(operand.IsShiftedRegister() && (operand.shift_amount() == 0));
4098  ccmpop = ConditionalCompareRegisterFixed | op | Rm(operand.reg());
4099  }
4100  Emit(SF(rn) | ccmpop | Cond(cond) | Rn(rn) | Nzcv(nzcv));
4101 }

4133 void Assembler::NEONModifiedImmShiftLsl(const VRegister& vd, const int imm8,
4134  const int left_shift,
4135  NEONModifiedImmediateOp op) {
4136  DCHECK(vd.Is8B() || vd.Is16B() || vd.Is4H() || vd.Is8H() || vd.Is2S() ||
4137  vd.Is4S());
4138  DCHECK((left_shift == 0) || (left_shift == 8) || (left_shift == 16) ||
4139  (left_shift == 24));
4140  DCHECK(is_uint8(imm8));
4141 
4142  int cmode_1, cmode_2, cmode_3;
4143  if (vd.Is8B() || vd.Is16B()) {
4144  DCHECK_EQ(op, NEONModifiedImmediate_MOVI);
4145  cmode_1 = 1;
4146  cmode_2 = 1;
4147  cmode_3 = 1;
4148  } else {
4149  cmode_1 = (left_shift >> 3) & 1;
4150  cmode_2 = left_shift >> 4;
4151  cmode_3 = 0;
4152  if (vd.Is4H() || vd.Is8H()) {
4153  DCHECK((left_shift == 0) || (left_shift == 8));
4154  cmode_3 = 1;
4155  }
4156  }
4157  int cmode = (cmode_3 << 3) | (cmode_2 << 2) | (cmode_1 << 1);
4158 
4159  Instr q = vd.IsQ() ? NEON_Q : 0;
4160 
4161  Emit(q | op | ImmNEONabcdefgh(imm8) | NEONCmode(cmode) | Rd(vd));
4162 }
4163 
4164 void Assembler::NEONModifiedImmShiftMsl(const VRegister& vd, const int imm8,
4165  const int shift_amount,
4166  NEONModifiedImmediateOp op) {
4167  DCHECK(vd.Is2S() || vd.Is4S());
4168  DCHECK((shift_amount == 8) || (shift_amount == 16));
4169  DCHECK(is_uint8(imm8));
4170 
4171  int cmode_0 = (shift_amount >> 4) & 1;
4172  int cmode = 0xC | cmode_0;
4173 
4174  Instr q = vd.IsQ() ? NEON_Q : 0;
4175 
4176  Emit(q | op | ImmNEONabcdefgh(imm8) | NEONCmode(cmode) | Rd(vd));
4177 }
4178 
4179 void Assembler::EmitShift(const Register& rd, const Register& rn, Shift shift,
4180  unsigned shift_amount) {
4181  switch (shift) {
4182  case LSL:
4183  lsl(rd, rn, shift_amount);
4184  break;
4185  case LSR:
4186  lsr(rd, rn, shift_amount);
4187  break;
4188  case ASR:
4189  asr(rd, rn, shift_amount);
4190  break;
4191  case ROR:
4192  ror(rd, rn, shift_amount);
4193  break;
4194  default:
4195  UNREACHABLE();
4196  }
4197 }
4198 
4199 void Assembler::EmitExtendShift(const Register& rd, const Register& rn,
4200  Extend extend, unsigned left_shift) {
4201  DCHECK(rd.SizeInBits() >= rn.SizeInBits());
4202  unsigned reg_size = rd.SizeInBits();
4203  // Use the correct size of register.
4204  Register rn_ = Register::Create(rn.code(), rd.SizeInBits());
4205  // Bits extracted are high_bit:0.
4206  unsigned high_bit = (8 << (extend & 0x3)) - 1;
4207  // Number of bits left in the result that are not introduced by the shift.
4208  unsigned non_shift_bits = (reg_size - left_shift) & (reg_size - 1);
4209 
4210  if ((non_shift_bits > high_bit) || (non_shift_bits == 0)) {
4211  switch (extend) {
4212  case UXTB:
4213  case UXTH:
4214  case UXTW:
4215  ubfm(rd, rn_, non_shift_bits, high_bit);
4216  break;
4217  case SXTB:
4218  case SXTH:
4219  case SXTW:
4220  sbfm(rd, rn_, non_shift_bits, high_bit);
4221  break;
4222  case UXTX:
4223  case SXTX: {
4224  DCHECK_EQ(rn.SizeInBits(), kXRegSizeInBits);
4225  // Nothing to extend. Just shift.
4226  lsl(rd, rn_, left_shift);
4227  break;
4228  }
4229  default:
4230  UNREACHABLE();
4231  }
4232  } else {
4233  // No need to extend as the extended bits would be shifted away.
4234  lsl(rd, rn_, left_shift);
4235  }
4236 }

4238 void Assembler::DataProcShiftedRegister(const Register& rd, const Register& rn,
4239  const Operand& operand, FlagsUpdate S,
4240  Instr op) {
4241  DCHECK(operand.IsShiftedRegister());
4242  DCHECK(rn.Is64Bits() || (rn.Is32Bits() && is_uint5(operand.shift_amount())));
4243  DCHECK(!operand.NeedsRelocation(this));
4244  Emit(SF(rd) | op | Flags(S) | ShiftDP(operand.shift()) |
4245  ImmDPShift(operand.shift_amount()) | Rm(operand.reg()) | Rn(rn) |
4246  Rd(rd));
4247 }
4248 
4249 void Assembler::DataProcExtendedRegister(const Register& rd, const Register& rn,
4250  const Operand& operand, FlagsUpdate S,
4251  Instr op) {
4252  DCHECK(!operand.NeedsRelocation(this));
4253  Instr dest_reg = (S == SetFlags) ? Rd(rd) : RdSP(rd);
4254  Emit(SF(rd) | op | Flags(S) | Rm(operand.reg()) |
4255  ExtendMode(operand.extend()) | ImmExtendShift(operand.shift_amount()) |
4256  dest_reg | RnSP(rn));
4257 }

4259 void Assembler::LoadStore(const CPURegister& rt, const MemOperand& addr,
4260  LoadStoreOp op) {
4261  Instr memop = op | Rt(rt) | RnSP(addr.base());
4262 
4263  if (addr.IsImmediateOffset()) {
4264  unsigned size_log2 = CalcLSDataSizeLog2(op);
4265  int offset = static_cast<int>(addr.offset());
4266  if (IsImmLSScaled(addr.offset(), size_log2)) {
4267  LoadStoreScaledImmOffset(memop, offset, size_log2);
4268  } else {
4269  DCHECK(IsImmLSUnscaled(addr.offset()));
4270  LoadStoreUnscaledImmOffset(memop, offset);
4271  }
4272  } else if (addr.IsRegisterOffset()) {
4273  Extend ext = addr.extend();
4274  Shift shift = addr.shift();
4275  unsigned shift_amount = addr.shift_amount();
4276 
4277  // LSL is encoded in the option field as UXTX.
4278  if (shift == LSL) {
4279  ext = UXTX;
4280  }
4281 
4282  // Shifts are encoded in one bit, indicating a left shift by the memory
4283  // access size.
4284  DCHECK(shift_amount == 0 || shift_amount == CalcLSDataSizeLog2(op));
4285  Emit(LoadStoreRegisterOffsetFixed | memop | Rm(addr.regoffset()) |
4286  ExtendMode(ext) | ImmShiftLS((shift_amount > 0) ? 1 : 0));
4287  } else {
4288  // Pre-index and post-index modes.
4289  DCHECK(IsImmLSUnscaled(addr.offset()));
4290  DCHECK_NE(rt, addr.base());
4291  int offset = static_cast<int>(addr.offset());
4292  if (addr.IsPreIndex()) {
4293  Emit(LoadStorePreIndexFixed | memop | ImmLS(offset));
4294  } else {
4295  DCHECK(addr.IsPostIndex());
4296  Emit(LoadStorePostIndexFixed | memop | ImmLS(offset));
4297  }
4298  }
4299 }

4305  DCHECK(IsEnabled(PMULL1Q) || vd.Is8H());

4317 bool Assembler::IsImmLSPair(int64_t offset, unsigned size) {
4318  bool offset_is_size_multiple =
4319  (static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<uint64_t>(offset >> size) << size) ==
4320  offset);
4321  return offset_is_size_multiple && is_int7(offset >> size);
4322 }
